<statement><div><p>The angle formed by the arms of an upright pair of dividers and the horizontal is <m>{45}^\circ</m>. The vertical distance from the horizontal to the vertex is <m>{13}\,\text{cm}</m>. Find the length of one arm of the divider without using a calculator or trigonometric tables.</p>
<p><m>\text{The Length of a divider arm from vertical height}=</m><fillin characters="7" name="ans1"/><m>\,\text{cm}</m></p></div></statement>
<solution><div><p><alert>Worked Solution:</alert></p>

<p>We are asked to find the length of one arm of the divider given:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Angle with horizontal: <m>{45}</m>Â°</li>
    <li>Vertical distance from horizontal to vertex: <m>{13}\, \text{cm}</m></li>
</ul>

<p>From trigonometry, for an upright divider forming an angle <m>\theta</m> with the horizontal, the relationship between the vertical height and the arm length is:</p>

<p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Arm length} \amp = \frac{\text{Vertical distance}}{\sin \theta}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{13}{\sin({45}^\circ)}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {13 \sqrt{2}} \text{ cm}</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>Hence, the length of one arm of the divider is <m>{13 \sqrt{2}}</m> cm.</p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>13 \sqrt{2}</m></p></answer>
